<plot>Leny Boeken: Almost 81 years old, but still working in a haberdashery shop, together with her son and granddaughter. Once per year, for 8 consecutive years now, she travels to places of her past. She's a jew and at the same time with Anne Frank, she was transported to one of the most horrible places mankind ever conceived. While family and shop business go on, Leny prepares for once again a journey to Poland.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?329318</url></doc>
